Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.05,0:00:03.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Last time on Fairy Tail...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.34,0:00:09.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We set out to find the parts of the clock, \Nand arrived at a giant crypt underneath a desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.94,0:00:13.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But all kinds of traps were \Nlying in wait for us there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.71,0:01:52.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're the ones from last time!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:54.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So you bastards are here too, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.50,0:01:58.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Samuel told us about "The \NKey of the Starry Heavens".
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.61,0:02:02.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And we know that a part of the clock is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.49,0:02:07.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like you haven't found \Nthe part yet either, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.69,0:02:14.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that Lulu-chama over there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.18,0:02:16.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who you callin' "Lulu-chama"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.43,0:02:18.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't call you that before...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.39,0:02:22.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,His pet name has gotten \Neven more embarrassing...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.01,0:02:25.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Encountering each other like this... \NIt's a fated reunion, indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.17,0:02:29.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's proof that we're joined \Nby the red string of fate!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.38,0:02:31.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not for you to decide!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.67,0:02:34.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,L-O-V-E!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.85,0:02:37.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna get you back for last time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.48,0:02:38.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roar...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.72,0:02:41.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...of the Fire Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.22,0:02:43.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have time to bother with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.93,0:02:48.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, I'm facing a major \Nturning point in my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.56,0:02:54.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hot-hot-hot-hot-hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.98,0:02:54.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy-neesan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.11,0:02:57.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu-nii, be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:03:00.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like before, he's got that \Ngreat nuisance of a shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.59,0:03:07.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.67,0:03:14.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Footprints of the Myth!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.43,0:03:20.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not chasing us...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.12,0:03:22.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we got lucky and they got buried.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.56,0:03:24.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like I planned!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.15,0:03:25.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.45,0:03:27.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, we've gotta search for that part!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.51,0:03:29.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.50,0:03:33.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lulu-chama, we need to \Nestablish the bond of love!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.78,0:03:36.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you stop calling me that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.06,0:03:40.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dan-san! Right now, finding \Nthat part takes priority!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.10,0:03:43.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We have an important duty to carry out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.85,0:03:48.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}know{\i0}! But love is important, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.85,0:03:50.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.12,0:03:53.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,L-O-V-E!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.24,0:03:55.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sick of hearin' that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.32,0:04:00.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hot-hot-hot-hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.62,0:04:00.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nee-san is on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.21,0:04:03.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap! I did it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.61,0:04:06.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anybody who dares interfere \Nwith two people in love
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.04,0:04:08.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,will get sliced up like a fish and \Nput back together on the table!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.95,0:04:11.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what he means...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.74,0:04:16.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Feel the might of my \Nmagic spear, Happy Lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.06,0:04:20.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Natsu-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:24.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you get hit, you'll shrink \Nagain like last time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.63,0:04:28.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it! I don't wanna \Nget trampled by you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.57,0:04:30.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not done yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.79,0:04:32.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nee-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.27,0:04:41.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.77,0:04:43.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.45,0:04:50.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me! I didn't mean to do it! \NI shrunk the woman that I love!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.34,0:04:54.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm a failure as a lover!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.77,0:04:57.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's how you feel, \Nthen get me back to normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:04:58.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.63,0:05:06.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.26,0:05:08.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This actually isn't so bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.48,0:05:14.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A tiny Lulu-chama has a charm \Nthat I'm reluctant to give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.13,0:05:17.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll keep you like this as my mascot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.55,0:05:19.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.36,0:05:21.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, I think I will leave you like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.69,0:05:26.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And when I get home, I'll put you on my \Ndesk and appreciate you at my leisure!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.08,0:05:28.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not room decoration!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.15,0:05:31.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This way, we'll always be together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.85,0:05:35.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's made Lucy-nee into a strap!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.87,0:05:38.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But she {\i1}is{\i0} cute like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.20,0:05:40.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I kind of want one myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.48,0:05:42.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop talking stupid and help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.85,0:05:47.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the woman that I love and I are \None! There is nothing that I fear!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.95,0:05:49.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's get back to what we were doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.44,0:05:57.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dan-san, attack him later! Right now, \Nwe've got to look for that part!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.04,0:06:01.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got him right where I \Nwant him! You go on ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.62,0:06:07.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Samuel-san didn't tell me any of the \Ndetails! I can't search without you, Dan-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.92,0:06:12.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?! We have to \Nhurry up and find that part, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.92,0:06:16.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't leave Lucy-neesan like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.01,0:06:24.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is making me dizzy! Oh, that's \Nright! The Celestial Spirits!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.55,0:06:26.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gate of the Archer, I open thee!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.83,0:06:28.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sagittarius!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.22,0:06:30.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You called-moshimoshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.00,0:06:35.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here-moshimoshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.42,0:06:39.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I, their owner, have been shrunken \Ndown, the Celestial Spirits are little, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.85,0:06:42.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I've been summoned,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.11,0:06:45.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's the duty of a Celestial Spirit \Nto aid the master, as it were-moshimoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.63,0:06:47.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this! I shall attack with all my might!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.79,0:06:54.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.64,0:06:59.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a little bone caught between my teeth \Nfrom the fish I had for breakfast this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.45,0:07:05.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I attacked with all my might, but it had \Nno effect on him, as it were-moshimoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.13,0:07:09.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I've got relief in my teeth, I'm \Ngoing to finish up here, starting with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.16,0:07:13.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out, Sagittarius!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.29,0:07:17.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! I stepped on another little one!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.46,0:07:20.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough. You can go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.24,0:07:24.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for not being of \Nany use, as it were-moshimoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.96,0:07:27.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not getting anywhere this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.45,0:07:28.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.77,0:07:35.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dan-san, what would you say to getting \Nmarried to Lucy-neesan right here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.64,0:07:37.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would we do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.79,0:07:43.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a holy place with a lot of history, \Nisn't it? I think it would be perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.40,0:07:45.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.83,0:07:47.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You know this is a graveyard...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.06,0:07:51.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's figure out the \Nbridal plan right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.53,0:07:53.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! I'll leave the details to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.75,0:08:01.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,First, we'll want to invite about 50 \Nfriends and relatives to the ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.17,0:08:04.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it'll be a gorgeous wedding!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.80,0:08:07.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For your honeymoon, you'll go \Non a 'round-the-world cruise!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.59,0:08:10.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How romantic!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.51,0:08:13.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You two will be happily married \Nfor the rest of your lives
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.30,0:08:18.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and will eventually become a constellation, the \NMarried Lovebirds, that decorates the night sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.66,0:08:20.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.66,0:08:24.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The dawn of my life is near!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.18,0:08:26.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't keep up with this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.69,0:08:29.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,L-O-V-E!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.70,0:08:32.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget about me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.02,0:08:39.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this smell?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.10,0:08:43.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It stinks! Romeo, you did this, didn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.79,0:08:47.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me! I'm doin' it \Nto help you, Lucy-nee!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.00,0:08:51.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It stinks so bad, I can't stand it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.05,0:08:54.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The smoke is trapped in my armor \Nand I think I'm gonna choke on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.54,0:09:04.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The red string that binds us...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.27,0:09:06.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy-nee!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.66,0:09:12.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hot-hot-hot-hot! How many times \Nhas this happened to me today?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.04,0:09:13.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy, get on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.60,0:09:17.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me back my wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.45,0:09:19.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You saved me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.45,0:09:22.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy, fly us right out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.64,0:09:23.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.90,0:09:28.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll return you to your original size! That \Nway, you'll both fall from the weight!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.49,0:09:39.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back to normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.00,0:09:47.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. I missed the target again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.99,0:09:50.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Happy is huge...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.27,0:09:52.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You suck!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.92,0:09:57.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dumbass! You're not really a master \Nlancer or anything, are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.25,0:10:00.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.61,0:10:08.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! I stepped on you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.40,0:10:12.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you did that on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.85,0:10:21.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure this is the right place?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.03,0:10:25.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is where it said on \Nthe map you fools gave me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.92,0:10:29.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can run faster than \Nanything on normal ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.15,0:10:32.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm out of my element \Nclimbing up a cliff!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.76,0:10:37.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't this be a lot easier if Lily \Njust gave us a lift to the top?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.21,0:10:41.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But if I did and there was a clue \Nalong the way, we would miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.53,0:10:44.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good choosing the easiest way. Mm-mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.32,0:10:49.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit bitching! I'll leave you hangin' here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.76,0:10:52.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Asshole. He really ticks me off...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.25,0:10:58.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... It seems like we're completely lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.24,0:11:03.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we've just been \Ngoing around in circles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.78,0:11:05.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the map?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.49,0:11:09.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't show the route in any detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.78,0:11:13.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are just instructions \Nto rely on the signs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.77,0:11:18.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's weird. If we keep going this way, \Nwe should reach our destination, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.53,0:11:22.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if the sign is wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.65,0:11:27.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That or maybe someone messed with the sign, \Npointing it in the wrong direction...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.43,0:11:29.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That kind of prank would be in bad taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.80,0:11:32.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a crime to change \Nthe direction of a sign,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.58,0:11:36.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,since if someone then makes a mistake, \Nit can lead to a major accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.47,0:11:41.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But we should be close. Let's keep moving \Nforward carefully while consulting the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.06,0:11:48.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if it is just a prank...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.85,0:11:51.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Or someone purposefully trying \Nto get us off track...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.13,0:12:13.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move, Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.10,0:12:16.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't fly, I'm likely \Nto stomp on you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.34,0:12:24.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a precious cultural heritage \Nsite! Don't carelessly destroy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.51,0:12:26.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now's no time to worry about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.10,0:12:29.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What a pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.85,0:12:31.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alrighty!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.61,0:12:39.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're already back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.94,0:12:42.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, {\i1}everyone's{\i0} back to normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.15,0:12:45.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, let's look for that clock part!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.60,0:12:47.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.41,0:12:52.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But how can we find it when we \Ndon't even know where it's hidden?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.37,0:12:56.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay. I brought the book \Nalong for a time like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.88,0:12:59.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It might provide us with a clue \Nthat leads us to the part!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.05,0:13:04.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If I had that book, maybe I'd even \Nbe able to find the part by myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.19,0:13:06.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me that book!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.76,0:13:07.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.43,0:13:09.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.64,0:13:11.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, while we have the chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.21,0:13:13.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Halt!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.45,0:13:14.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You{\i0} halt!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.28,0:13:19.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kick his ass! In the \Nmeantime, search for the part!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.39,0:13:21.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it! Leave it to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.26,0:13:23.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Careful you don't get stepped on!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.75,0:13:26.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you're not around, \NI ain't gettin' stepped on!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.73,0:13:27.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.83,0:13:31.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you get in my way {\i1}again{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.07,0:13:34.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is gonna be the last time!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.29,0:13:38.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.99,0:13:40.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Get away from us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.30,0:13:46.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy-neesan, where's the part?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.22,0:13:50.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... um... ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.78,0:13:55.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.15,0:14:02.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What a time to run out of magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.76,0:14:06.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.77,0:14:09.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Grab on!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.69,0:14:15.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse to accept mercy from the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.34,0:14:18.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stubborn! Just hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.33,0:14:33.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy-neesan, are you alright?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.30,0:14:35.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in one piece...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.29,0:14:38.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on! I'll come down to help you out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.25,0:14:46.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't! Hurry up and find the part \Ninstead! We'll regroup somewhere eventually!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.16,0:14:52.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Will she really be okay? After all, that \NCoco girl is down there with her...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.55,0:14:56.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy has her Celestial Spirits, so I'd \Nsay there's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.34,0:15:00.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Let's do as Lucy-nee told us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.95,0:15:03.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy-neesan, be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.93,0:15:05.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.67,0:15:07.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.50,0:15:09.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.83,0:15:11.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mind your own business!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.43,0:15:13.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you hadn't reached out \Nto me in the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.54,0:15:15.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would've been able to \Nget back up on my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.10,0:15:19.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how you talk to someone \Nwho tried to help you out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.89,0:15:22.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I never asked for any help!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.06,0:15:25.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not nice at all, are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.24,0:15:30.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know someone who looks just like \Nyou, but she's a good, honest girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.15,0:15:35.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's {\i1}not{\i0} me, so \Ndon't confuse me with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.04,0:15:44.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you people aiming to do anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.72,0:15:47.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you gonna do if you \Ncollect all the clock parts?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.42,0:15:50.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by "crusade" and "chaos"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.42,0:15:55.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I would tell you! The question is, \Nwhy are {\i1}you people{\i0} getting in our way?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.27,0:16:00.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know {\i1}what's{\i0} going on, so we're \Njust trying to investigate the situation!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.40,0:16:03.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever you're trying to \Ndo, it's a waste of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.59,0:16:07.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A bunch of cut-rate wizards \Nlike you could never stop us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.90,0:16:10.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, is she nasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.10,0:16:19.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful! There could be a trap anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.27,0:16:20.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}know{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.04,0:16:24.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The traps are meant for tomb \Nraiders like you and your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.61,0:16:27.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're doing the same thing we are!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.29,0:16:31.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.68,0:16:36.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.36,0:16:42.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No need to thank me. I was just paying \Nyou back for trying to help me before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.52,0:16:51.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You really aren't honest about your feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.55,0:16:57.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you have the same face and \Nthe same speed as the Coco from Edolas...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.19,0:17:00.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she really that much like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.54,0:17:03.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I mean, you really are \Njust about the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.81,0:17:09.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a long story, but in the \Nbeginning, {\i1}we{\i0} were enemies, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.59,0:17:12.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, though, we became friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.61,0:17:19.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's where we differ. There's no \Nway you and I are going to be friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.64,0:17:24.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, it's not as if we \Nwant to interfere with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.85,0:17:28.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We just think that if it's going to cause \Ntrouble for a great number of people,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.41,0:17:29.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,we have to put a stop to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.42,0:17:32.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that your aim?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.42,0:17:39.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, in my case, I also want to find \Nout what my father was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.28,0:17:44.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father... Mr. Jude Heartfilia, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.70,0:17:46.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He was supposed to be a brilliant \Nentrepreneur, I believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.85,0:17:51.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm his daughter, but I didn't \Nreally know him well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.23,0:17:58.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm perplexed as to why he would even go \Nthrough the trouble of hiding the parts...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.18,0:18:02.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wish he would've been a little more \Nempathetic about the people hunting them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.40,0:18:04.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm with you on that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.78,0:18:08.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.54,0:18:13.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing. I was just \Nthinking you're a funny girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.11,0:18:15.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that an insult?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.82,0:18:19.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't mean it like that... Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.31,0:18:25.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A dead end... I wonder if we \Nshould retrace our steps...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.95,0:18:30.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a deep thinker, are you? There's always \Nsome kind of switch in a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.60,0:18:34.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.46,0:18:43.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Coco!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.40,0:18:49.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Coco! Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.58,0:18:52.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.94,0:18:57.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness! You're alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.61,0:19:00.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! We'll pull you up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.28,0:19:30.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You should've just left that jerk as she was!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.77,0:19:33.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind! Let's just hurry \Nup and look for the part!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.86,0:19:41.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,According to Lucy, the clock \Npart should be right here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.71,0:19:46.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see anything that looks \Nlike it could be part of a clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.27,0:19:54.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We finally made it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.12,0:19:56.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The air's thin up here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.20,0:19:58.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.13,0:20:02.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We ain't got time to take a break. \NLet's search for that part!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.11,0:20:04.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, just a few minutes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.51,0:20:06.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even take a single step...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.88,0:20:08.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starving...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.79,0:20:10.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! We're on the wrong mountain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.02,0:20:16.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The part's on the mountain over there! \NWe've gotta climb up that one!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.40,0:20:19.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.81,0:20:23.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.35,0:20:32.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I meant to encourage everyone \Nwith my little joke...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.46,0:20:34.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems to have had the opposite effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.25,0:20:37.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not seeing anythin' like a part.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.34,0:20:42.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it's probably buried \Nsomewhere 'round here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.46,0:20:45.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.69,0:21:00.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it! We've found it at last!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.73,0:21:05.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's said that this place contains books \Non magic from all times and places...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.45,0:21:07.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Library...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.70,0:21:10.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Another huge building...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.70,0:21:15.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it looks like not \Nmany people come here...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.21,0:21:19.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What a waste. Even though it's a \Nrepository of knowledge from the past...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.34,0:21:30.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,These are all books on magic?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.64,0:21:35.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's even more impressive than I imagined!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.57,0:21:38.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Levy-san would love it here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.06,0:21:41.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But all of the books are so old...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.28,0:21:58.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roar of the Fire Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.30,0:22:07.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have all day to waste on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.05,0:22:09.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my line!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.18,0:22:11.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is going to end it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.85,0:22:15.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And when you succumb, I'll \Nsee you plunge into a ditch!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.22,0:22:19.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I ain't gonna succumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.91,0:23:58.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm smellin' something familiar...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.89,0:23:59.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A smell?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.54,0:24:03.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The smell of someone who helped \Nme before when I had motion sickness...?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.28,0:24:04.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Or wait, he attacked me...?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.99,0:24:07.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are two totally different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.06,0:24:10.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the person a good guy or bad guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.09,0:24:11.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, let's split the difference
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.55,0:24:13.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and say he's a minor villain who \Nacts worse than he really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.11,0:24:16.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: True Evil Revisited!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.60,0:24:19.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So what does it smell like?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.20,0:24:22.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the smell of \Nblack full body tights...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.49,0:24:24.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a smell for that?!
